</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwisbus2k1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wisbus2k1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 10:48:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> I've been playing since late July, 1999.  I went through a Paladin, Druid, Warrior and Necromancer before I finally settled on the Magician, who was made on a different server. <br>
<br>
I liked being isolated from my old server.  I started over - no Oracle robe, no Glowing Black Stone, nothing like that.  I was a completely independent character in a new and foreign world. <br>
<br>
I made a magician because necros didn't like them so much on their board. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I wanted to see what all the hubbub was about.  I haven't been let down - sure, there are dry times, but they don't last for 3+ years, much like some others on this board. <br>
<br>
I built a good rep around myself in Velks Lab, back when I was doing the run to 60 over a year ago - back when I didn't have my epic.  When I'd go LFG, people would pick me up most of the time. If not, I'd solo or make my own group.  Recently, I've been getting nightly invites to CT sewer groups from people I don't know - it's kind of neat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I raid stuff, too.  I've had an Emp fight with one other mage.  Yeah, I was making rods almost the entire fight, we had enough to win - it was awesome!  I was a solo mage on a HP fight, and I had time to make rods and nuke / rain for ~50k as well as use my pet.  My group got exp, and I received our 60 heal.<br>
<br>
The mage class is a very complex one.  We're built on old principles: pet, nuke, summon.  Those old principles are still with us today, in a more dynamic world and larger, more involved battles such as Emp - AHR.  For some it?s hard to see any of the first two, some guilds recruit only mages for mod rods. That?s not the mages fault, or the mage class in general - it's the guilds.   <br>
<br>
I still do damage, more than our fair share - I feel. I have never needed pet parses, or nuke comparisons vs. other classes to feel powerful.  I've had a feeling of being powerful since level 8, back when I killed my first puma and it's still with me today.  <br>
<br>
I don't see the problems some others do with their mages on raids.  I'm not a mod rod bitch when I raid.  I actively use my pet, and nuke along with making <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Happy Panda Fireworks</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and flare staves for myself and some others; they're fun!.  <br>
<br>
I have my own style, and it mixes well with raid encounters.  I work harder than a &quot;rod bitch&quot; who spends the entire time dropping t-rods near a wall. I take on 2-3+ more jobs during a raid on top of making rods. Those worthless AA skills called <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Quick Summoning, Spell Casting Mastery and Spell Casting Fury</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> help make my night more productive and eventful for all those around me.<br>
<br>
Mages still have plenty of power.  It may not be as showing as a 5k critical off GSS, or a 2k double backstab from the rouges - but being the backbone of an entire raid, to having offensive potential with utility support is such a great combination. <br>
<br>
Glad I'm a mage!<br>
<br>
Wisbus<br>
Tunare<br>
