<br>
I too believe the Mage class has been hamstrung. Are we worthless, no. Are we powerless, no. Are we what we should be, hell no. Can we still play and have fun as a Mage, yes.<br>
<br>
I have been a supporter for revamping the Mage class all together. We are Elementalist, therefore we should be able to be masters of the elements. If we fight a fire based creature, we chould have water and earth spells that conteract that creatures power. A fire bolt should never be used against a Fire Elemental. (See my point?)<br>
<br>
If I am being groomed to be a Merchant, then VI should upgrade my mana and natural medding so at least I can do some good in a group. I have no problem standing in the background with the clerics, but I don't have the mana or the medding skills to be much good for very long.<br>
<br>
As far as I can see we are a hodgepoge of mediocre skills. We are masters of nothing and a poor jack-of-all-trades. I constanly see players of other classes 7 to 8 levels below me kill faster and more often than I can.<br>
<br>
I really like playing my Mage, and I will continue to do so for many months to come. However, I see a time when my Mage will become the supplier to other characters I will develop. Unless we baraged VI with our concerns, nothing will change. In reality, unless something is done soon, EQ will be ignored and will remain as is forever when EQ2 comes out.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts from a ranting ole' fart.<br>
