And I disagree with your example of past historical documents. 1) It's possible to make an unbiased history. 2) Just because past historical documents have done it, doesn't make it okay to do it 3) Just because past historical documents have done it, doesn't mean it's wrong for me to speak out against it.<br>
<br>
If you don't think arguing semantics is a speed bump, look at how useless the entire semantics conversation has been. It will never arrive anywhere and doesn't contribute more than a tedious sub-argument. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaldiinaredhelistar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naldiin Aredhelistar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(10/4/02 4:01:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=335.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with the original post entirely.<br>
<br>
I didn't pick to play a magician so that I could use a single spell (Trod) and simply play vending machine.  <br>
I don't see a magician as a bent old man picking up Trods and dropping them again while everyone else fights.<br>
<br>
I don't see magicians as a one way raid-bus-service using CotH.<br>
<br>
I *do* see mages as a swirling maelstrom of elemental death, between pets, nukes, DSs PB nukes, etc.<br>
<br>
That is why I chose to play as a magician.  To be a damage dealer, to devistate opponents with my offensive spells and a powerful minion...<br>
<br>
Well, after the changes to our class, I'm reduced to Trods and chainpetting.  My best nukes don't work in a raid situation, and because they're not lures, won't stick on many things even if they did work.  Magician mana, to put it simply, is a thousand times more useful in your cleric/necro/druid/wizard/enchanter's mana bar.<br>
<br>
That alone should be tricking alarms at VI, that my class is useless to the point that our high end role consists of giving our mana away to others.<br>
<br>
Perhaps this new round of balencing will restore mages to the role of damage dealer again.  Perhaps PoP will have something useful for us.  But I just don't see it happening.  So far, changes have been applied in magnitude of the player-base-clout.  And because there are so few mages, we have extreamly little clout.<br>
<br>
And, if VI acts as they always have, that means we will get very little attention.<br>
<br>
Just to clarify and sum up, my issue with the mage class is not that we arn't useful enough (although the point could be argued, it already has been, and I won't insult your intelligance by doing so again), but that our role has so changed...to be frank, &quot;This isn't what I signed up for.&quot;<br>
<br>
Clerics still heal, wizards still nuke, warriors still tank, however the mage play style has changed from a damage dealing role to support.  I wanted to be a damage dealer, and I don't want to start over as a wizard.  Mages are supposed to be the second best nukers, VI has maintained that we are (cough) and thats the role I signed up for.<br>
<br>
I didn't join the artilliary to load some infantry man's machine gun.<br>
<br>
I joined the artilliary to fire a cannon.<br>
<br>
Baron Naldiin Aredhel'Istar<br>
58th Conjuror<br>
